    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter opening the pager with some commands, the cursor will be placed in the middle of a line:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/468c16c6-33b0-4771-9750-ad2a4c339321\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable {}`\n- `:hi`\n- `g<`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor is either at column 1 or the final column of line one (the equivalent of `0` or `$`).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2246+g57fc77ed29\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo (`make`)",
